      • getInferenceParameters

        InferenceParameters getInferenceParameters()
        Returns the inference parameters for this query. Individual inference parameters may be modified on the InferenceParameters object.

        For convenience, several of the most commonly used inference parameters may be also accessed from getters and setters which are directly on the Query object. Those parameters are:

        • inferenceMode (:INFERENCE-MODE)
        • maxAnswerCount (:MAX-NUMBER)
        • maxTime (:MAX-TIME)
        • maxTransformationDepth (:MAX-TRANSFORMATION-DEPTH)
        Specified by:
        getInferenceParameters in interface QuerySpecification<T extends QuerySpecification>
        Returns:
        the inference parameters

      • setSubstitutions

        T setSubstitutions(Map<KbObject,Object> substitutions)
        Applies substitutions to the original query. This method will undo any substitutions which had previously been applied. To apply additional substitutions, use addSubstitutions(java.util.Map). Indexical terms are frequently replaced in Sentences, particularly in Query sentences, so you may want to see KbObject.isIndexical() for more details about them. However, this method can be used to replace any KbObjects within a Sentence, not just indexicals.
        Parameters:
        substitutions -
        Returns:
        this query
        See Also:
        KbObject.isIndexical(), Sentence.getIndexicals(boolean), Sentence.replaceTerms(java.util.Map), com.cyc.query.QuerySpecification#addSubstitutions(java.util.Map), QuerySpecification.getSubstitutions(), QuerySpecification.getUnresolvedIndexicals(), com.cyc.query.Indexicals

      • addSubstitutions

      • setInferenceMode

        T setInferenceMode(InferenceMode mode)
        Set the inference mode. Inference modes are meant to be intuitive measures of how hard Cyc should work to answer a query. Setting the inference mode sets various other low-level parameters to appropriate values for that mode, but explictly setting values for such parameters overrides values set by the mode.

        This method is a trampoline to QuerySpecification#getInferenceParameters()#setInferenceMode(com.cyc.query.parameters.InferenceMode).

        Parameters:
        mode -
        Returns:
        this object
        See Also:
        for more parameters

      • setMaxAnswerCount

        T setMaxAnswerCount(Integer maxAnswers)
        Set the maximum number of answers (or sets of answers) that Cyc will attempt to find for the Query. In some cases (such as when a set of answers is retrieved in a batch), more answers than this may actually be returned. Once this number of answers has been reached, Cyc will not actively look for additional answers.

        A value of null means the inference will continue until it exhausts or some other limit is reached.

        This method is a trampoline to QuerySpecification#getInferenceParameters()#setMaxAnswerCount(java.lang.Integer).

        Parameters:
        maxAnswers - number of answers
        Returns:
        this object
        See Also:
        for more parameters

      • setMaxTime

        T setMaxTime(Integer maxSeconds)
        Set the max time value (in seconds). Setting this parameter to some number licenses Cyc to stop work on an inference once it has been working on it for at least that many seconds.

        A value of null means the inference will continue until it exhausts or some other limit is reached.

        This method is a trampoline to QuerySpecification#getInferenceParameters()#setMaxTime(java.lang.Integer).

        Parameters:
        maxSeconds - timeout value in seconds
        Returns:
        this object
        See Also:
        for more parameters

      • setMaxTransformationDepth

        T setMaxTransformationDepth(Integer depth)
        Set the max transformation depth value. Setting this parameter to some number prevents Cyc from reasoning using chains of rules longer than that number.

        This method is a trampoline to QuerySpecification#getInferenceParameters()#setMaxTransformationDepth(java.lang.Integer).

      • setQuerySentenceHypothesizedClause

        T setQuerySentenceHypothesizedClause(Sentence sentence)
        Sets the hypothesized clause of this Query. When the query is run, Cyc will assume that this clause is true. If the clause is independently known to be false in the query context, the query will be considered tautologous, and will fail.
        Parameters:
        sentence -
        Returns:
        this Query
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if query has already been started
